Several international financial authorities offer specific guidelines for determining nonperforming loans.

The <a data-component="link" data-ordinal="1" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" href="https://www.investopedia.com/terms/e/europeancentralbank.asp">European Central Bank</a> (ECB) requires asset and definition comparability to evaluate risk exposures across euro area <a data-component="link" data-ordinal="2" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" href="https://www.investopedia.com/terms/c/centralbank.asp">central banks</a>. The ECB specifies multiple criteria that can cause an NPL classification when it performs stress tests on participating banks.

